<http://www.spektrix.com/thecultch/event/137801ANKNJSBGDLMDRBBPLKPTSHBBCLB> a schema:Event;
  schema:name "For Frances when it's raining";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">Presented by The Cultch</span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Produced by Amiel Gladstone and Veda Hille (Vancouver)</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Historic Theatre 1895 Venables St.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>From acclaimed creators Amiel Gladstone and Veda Hille comes <span class=\"ItalicText\">For Frances when it’s raining</span>, a mesmerizing new musical adapted from Kathryn Davis’s acclaimed novel <span class=\"ItalicText\">The Girl Who Trod on a Loaf</span>. Blending Davis’s surreal, evocative storytelling with Hille and Gladstone’s genre-bending score and inventive theatricality, the show follows a young singer whose small town world tilts into the strange and sublime when a passionate composer appears and sends her spiralling into an uncanny realm.  Darkly funny, deeply haunting, and musically thrilling, this is a bold exploration of art, ambition, and the stories we inherit. Can music save our lives?<span><br/></span>
""";
