<http://www.spektrix.com/thecultch/event/156601APDSPQKGJNQPPJJPTGBGPRPPHLS> a schema:Event;
  schema:name "The Horse Of Jenin";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">The Cultch and Rumble Theatre present</span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">By Alaa Shehada</span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Produced by Troupe Courage (Amsterdam) with 55B Productions (USA)</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Canadian Premiere</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">The horse in Arabic is a symbol of freedom.<span><br/></span>But to us, this horse is much more. This horse is us.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Built from the debris of a major invasion, the Horse of Jenin sculpture became a constant presence in Alaa’s life growing up in Occupied Palestine. It stood proudly in the center of the city for twenty years, symbolizing hope and resistance.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Then, on OCT 29, 2023, an Israeli bulldozer entered the city, ripping the sculpture from its place — and from its people.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Now, Alaa is left wondering… What happened to the horse?<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Combining storytelling, mask and stand-up comedy, <span class=\"ItalicText\">The Horse of Jenin</span> explores the everyday life of a boy growing up in Jenin in Occupied Palestine who, like every child in the world, just wants to play and have fun.<span><br/></span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-10-08T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/thecultch/files/e8ce49ec-eaf2-46e7-8506-273eeb91bff5.jpg>;
  schema:location <https://spektrix.com/thecultch/location/601APNNMRMBJQQPBSCNQGQHGKKCRPSSGN>;
  schema:offers _:c5a4b28f60d54d888edb71ae5e343b023562;
  schema:duration "PT60M";
  schema:endDate "2026-10-08T20:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

